<item>
            <title>[FLINK-21933] [kinesis][efo] EFO consumer treats interrupts as retryable exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21933</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Background&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
When an Flink job is cancelled or failed, the source threads get interrupted. The EFO consumer is treating this exception as retryable and will retry until MAX_RETRIES is exceeded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scope&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Update error handling to treat Interrupted exceptions as non-recoverable. The source should gracefully shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
